        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
            <h4>How long does the henna stain last?</h4>
            <div class="faq-toggle">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">With proper aftercare, bridal henna typically lasts 2–4 weeks. The initial dark color develops over 24–48 hours. Avoiding water on the design for the first 8–12 hours is key for the deepest stain.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
            <h4>Is your henna 100% natural?</h4>
            <div class="faq-toggle">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes! I only use 100% natural henna powder sourced from Rajasthan, India, mixed with eucalyptus oil, lemon juice, and sugar. No chemicals, no "black henna," no PPD — completely safe for all skin types including sensitive skin.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
            <h4>When should I schedule my bridal appointment?</h4>
            <div class="faq-toggle">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">I recommend booking your bridal mehndi 1–2 days before the wedding ceremony (Nikah/Shaadi day) so the color develops fully. I suggest booking your date 3–6 months in advance as peak wedding season fills up quickly.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
            <h4>Do you travel to my venue?</h4>
            <div class="faq-toggle">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Absolutely! I travel to your home, venue, or hotel throughout Ontario. Travel fees apply for locations beyond 30km from my base in Ontario. I'm available province-wide and can arrange travel for destination events.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
            <h4>How long does the application take?</h4>
            <div class="faq-toggle">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Full bridal (both hands + feet) typically takes 3–5 hours depending on design complexity. Simple event henna is 5–15 minutes per person. I always confirm timing during your consultation so we plan your day perfectly.</div>
        </div>
